When the king Gaturanicus had given all that he had to poor men and to churches, he sent a priest for to fetch to him of the relies of this holy company. And as he returned with the relies, the tempest arose in the lake of Lausanne in such wise that the ship was in peril; he set the chasse with the relics against the waves of water, and anon the tempest ceased and the waves of the water were appeased.
